### =============================================================================
### GW2 API - NexusRaidClears registration tests
### VS Code extension: humao.rest-client (REST Client)
### https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client
###
### Usage:
###   1. Paste your API key(s) into the config section below.
###   2. Set @activeApiKey to the variable you want to exercise.
###   3. Click "Send Request" above any ### section.
###
### Registration flow (matches AccountRegistry::BuildProfile):
###   tokeninfo -> account -> characters
### Required permissions: account, progression, characters
### =============================================================================

@baseUrl = https://api.guildwars2.com

# --- API keys ---
# Add one @variable per GW2 API key. Keep keys out of git if this file is committed.
@apiKeyPrimary = PASTE-YOUR-API-KEY-HERE
@apiKeySecondary =

# Switch between keys by changing this line only.
@activeApiKey = {{apiKeyPrimary}}

# Shorthand used by all requests below.
@apiKey = {{activeApiKey}}


### =============================================================================
### Registration step 1 - Validate token / read permissions
### GET /v2/tokeninfo
###
### Success: 200
### Body fields: id, name, permissions[]
### permissions must include: account, progression, characters
### =============================================================================

# @name tokeninfo
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/tokeninfo
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


### =============================================================================
### Registration step 2 - Fetch account name
### GET /v2/account
###
### Success: 200
### Body field used by addon: name
### Requires permission: account
### =============================================================================

# @name account
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/account
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


### =============================================================================
### Registration step 3 - Fetch character names (CORRECT endpoint)
### GET /v2/characters
###
### Success: 200
### Body: JSON array of strings, e.g. ["My Ranger", "My Mesmer"]
### Requires permission: characters
###
### This is what NexusRaidClears expects and stores in api_accounts.json.
### =============================================================================

# @name characters
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/characters
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


### =============================================================================
### Registration step 3 (alternate) - Full character objects
### GET /v2/characters?ids=all
###
### Success: 200
### Body: JSON array of objects; each object has a "name" field (plus race, level, etc.)
### Requires permission: characters
###
### NOT what the addon parses today - included for comparison/debugging only.
### =============================================================================

# @name charactersAll
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/characters?ids=all
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


### =============================================================================
### Known-bad endpoint (old bug)
### GET /v2/account/characters
###
### Failure: 404
### Body: {"text":"not found"}
###
### This endpoint does not exist. Iterating that JSON object produced characters:
### ["not found"]
### =============================================================================

# @name charactersWrongEndpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/account/characters
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json


### =============================================================================
### Optional - test secondary API key (duplicate registration flow)
### Set @activeApiKey = {{apiKeySecondary}} at the top, or override locally:
### =============================================================================

# @name tokeninfoSecondary
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/tokeninfo
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKeySecondary}}
Accept: application/json

###
# @name accountSecondary
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/account
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKeySecondary}}
Accept: application/json

###
# @name charactersSecondary
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/characters
Authorization: Bearer {{apiKeySecondary}}
Accept: application/json
